The paper focuses on the visualization of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the training and functioning of CNNs, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper leverages the capability of co-processing from Paraview, which is a tool commonly used in scientific simulations, suggesting a possible fit with cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the potential use of visualization to adjust the architecture of networks or compress pre-trained networks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
